One man was killed, and another two seriously injured, when three men attacked a mosque in Verulam, KwaZulu-Natal just before 3PM yesterday. In addition to those injuries, the Imam Hussain Mosque in Old Main Road in Ottawa was also set alight, reports News24. Three Egyptian men are believed to be behind the attack, which comes just days before the start of the holy month of Ramadan. Before we get to that video, here’s Prem Balram from Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa), a private security company that responded to the attack:  A warning that the footage below is very disturbing:  According to KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala, police are investigating three counts of attempted murder and arson. Gwala also added that the motives of the attack are unclear. The Daily Maverick have more on what transpired: Condolences to all those affected by this heinous attack. [sources:news24&dailymav]   Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 2oceansvibe.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.